Design and développementLe S. 19 is a seaplane, single seat, biplane with an engine mounted on struts between the hull and the upper wing. The engine Ansaldo San Giorgio 4E-29L'Aviation: RAIS seaplane race (Race hydroplanes RAIS) 500 hp is equipped with a pusher propeller bladed. Small floats of stabilization are mounted under the lower wing.
History opérationnelleLe engine of the S. 19 was not ready in time for the Trophy Schneider 1920, the aircraft could not, therefore, not participate in it.
